Baroin Says Financial Transaction Tax Is Technically Feasible

-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-09-24T00:31:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/baroin-says-financial-transaction-tax-is-technically-feasible.html
French Finance Minister  Francois
Baroin  said today that a financial transaction tax is
technically feasible and could fund development. Speaking as the
current head of the Group of 20 nations, Baroin told a news
conference in  Washington  that the G-20 aims to increase  food
security  and reduce imbalances.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Deen in Paris at 
 markdeen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
 kcostelloe@bloomberg.net  